-- Vedanta Zambian Workers Win 17% Pay Rise, Reuters Says
-- B y   A l a s t a i r   R e e d
-- 2012-01-27T08:18:27Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-27/vedanta-zambian-workers-win-17-pay-rise-reuters-says-correct-.html
(Corrects spelling of company name in headline.)  Konkola Copper Mines Plc, the
Zambian miner owned by  Vedanta Resources Plc (VED) , agreed to give
workers a 17 percent pay increase backdated to the start of the
year, Reuters reported, citing the Mineworkers Union of  Zambia .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Alastair Reed at   areed12@bloomberg.net  